<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="iddd31ad91-3a6e-11f1-a0f3-db3efcbbb4ee" identifier="/us/usc/t2/s5603"><num value="5603">§ 5603.</num><heading> Symbol of office of Sergeant at Arms</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The symbol of his office shall be the mace, which shall be borne by him while enforcing order on the floor.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="iddd31ad92-3a6e-11f1-a0f3-db3efcbbb4ee">(<ref href="/us/act/1890-10-01/ch1256/s2">Oct. 1, 1890, ch. 1256, § 2</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/26/645">26 Stat. 645</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="iddd31ad93-3a6e-11f1-a0f3-db3efcbbb4ee">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="iddd31ad94-3a6e-11f1-a0f3-db3efcbbb4ee"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I76" topic="codification" id="iddd31ad95-3a6e-11f1-a0f3-db3efcbbb4ee"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Codification</heading>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Section was formerly classified to <ref href="/us/usc/t2/s79">section 79 of this title</ref> prior to editorial reclassification and renumbering as this section.</p>
</note>
